Content:
This is anything but minimalist.<p>Why do I need a slower plugin manager that requires editing .vimrc to enable/disable plugins, when a couple of simple shell commands is faster and less error prone?<p><pre><code>  vimenable() { mv $VIM_DISABLED/$1 $VIM_BUNDLE }
  vimdisable() { mv $VIM_BUNDLE/$1 $VIM_DISABLED }
  vimupdate() { for p in $VIM_BUNDLE/*; do (cd $p; git pull); done }
</code></pre>
The dependent plugin support is interesting but until all the plugins include a standard dependency spec, I have to do it manually anyway.
